  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CompressionProcess">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">compression process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de compressão</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A planned process in which the pressure of a gas is increased by reducing its volume through mechanical work applied by petroleum production equipment.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000108">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diaphragm valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de diafragma</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab745"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab744"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Since this is a constructive type defined by physical mechanism (diaphragm closure), necessary conditions are used to avoid over-classification under the Open World Assumption. Not every equipment with a diaphragm component should automatically be classified as a diaphragm valve - the structural differentia requires domain validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diaphragm valve is a valve that uses a resilient diaphragm forced against a port as its closure mechanism to control fluid flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de diafragma é uma válvula que usa um diafragma resiliente forçado contra uma porta como seu mecanismo de fechamento para controlar o fluxo de fluido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A diaphragm valve is a valve that uses a resilient diaphragm forced against a port as its closure mechanism to control fluid flow.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every diaphragm valve is a valve that has a resilient diaphragm as component part and has a port as component part and participates in diaphragm closure processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DiaphragmValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃d,p (ResilientDiaphragm(d) ∧ Port(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab525">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab523"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SupportFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab169"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab170"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">support function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de suporte</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A designed function borne by petroleum production equipment whose realization constitutes the bearing of mechanical loads from attached components or piping to maintain their position and structural integrity.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab2465">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab2467"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab215">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000026"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab1888">
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab1886"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab451">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000200"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000090">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pressure vessel</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">vaso de pressão</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pressure vessel is a vessel that has a pressure containment function, and every vessel with a pressure containment function is a pressure vessel.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab2144"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A pressure vessel is a vessel that bears a pressure containment function, designed to safely withstand internal and/or external pressure loads.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um vaso de pressão é um vaso que possui uma função de contenção sob pressão, projetado para suportar com segurança cargas de pressão internas e/ou externas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pressure vessel is a vessel that bears a pressure containment function, designed to safely withstand internal and/or external pressure loads.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (PressureVessel(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f (PressureContainmentFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TubingBundle">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">tubing bundle</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">feixe de coluna de produção</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">An assembly of multiple tubing strings grouped and routed together for injection or production purposes in petroleum production wells or risers.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000292">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gravity separator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">separador gravitacional</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gravity separator is a separator that bears a GravitySeparationFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um separador gravitacional é um separador que realiza separação baseada nas diferenças de gravidade específica das substâncias sendo separadas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gravity separator is a separator that performs separation based on differences in specific gravity of the substances being separated.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A gravity separator is a separator that performs separation based on differences in specific gravity of the substances being separated.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GravitySeparator(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(GravitySeparationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab1413"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/UninterruptedPowerSupplyFunction">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab2684"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab2683"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de fornecimento ininterrupto de energia</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">uninterrupted power supply function</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A designed function borne by petroleum production equipment whose realization constitutes the provision of continuous electrical power to critical loads during interruptions to the main power supply.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab109">
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000157"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab110"/>
  </rdf:Description>
