  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/VibrationSignal">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A measurement information content entity constituting an electrical signal representing the amplitude or frequency of mechanical vibration measured in petroleum production equipment.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MeasurementInformationContentEntity"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">sinal de vibração</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vibration signal</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab1111">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/WasteGasDisposalFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab1184">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000082"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MechanicalLoad">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A quality inhering in a material entity, constituting the aggregate mechanical force or moment applied to a structural component of petroleum production equipment.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">mechanical load</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">carga mecânico</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000019"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000285">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000264"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab1303"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gas engine is an engine that has gaseous fuel portion as input and has spark ignition system as component part at all times and has reciprocating piston mechanism as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A gas engine is an engine that uses gaseous fuel as input, employs a spark ignition system, and operates with a reciprocating piston mechanism to generate mechanical energy.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas engine</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">motor a gás</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Gas engine is defined by constructive characteristics (gaseous fuel, spark ignition, reciprocating mechanism) rather than a unique function. Under Open World Assumption, making these conditions sufficient could lead to false positives where complex hybrid engines or experimental designs with these features are automatically classified as standard gas engines when they might require different maintenance/operational categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um motor a gás é um motor que usa combustível gasoso como entrada, emprega um sistema de ignição por centelha e opera com um mecanismo de pistão alternativo para gerar energia mecânica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gas engine is an engine that uses gaseous fuel as input, employs a spark ignition system, and operates with a reciprocating piston mechanism to generate mechanical energy.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GasEngine(x) → Engine(x) ∧ ∃f,s,r(GaseousFuelPortion(f) ∧ SparkIgnitionSystem(s) ∧ ReciprocatingPistonMechanism(r) ∧ hasInput(x,f) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,r)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000083">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow modification accessory</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">MaterialArtifact que possui uma FlowModificationFunction e</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that bears a FlowModificationFunction and that is used as a component in flow control assemblies to alter the characteristics of fluid flow such as velocity profile, turbulence, or pressure distribution.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab1218"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que possui uma FlowModificationFunction e que é usado como componente em conjuntos de controle de fluxo para alterar as características do fluxo de fluido, como perfil de velocidade, turbulência ou distribuição de pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that bears a FlowModificationFunction and that is used as a component in flow control assemblies to alter the characteristics of fluid flow such as velocity profile, turbulence, or pressure distribution.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flow modification accessory is a MaterialArtifact that bears a FlowModificationFunction and participates in processes that alter fluid flow characteristics.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlowModificationAccessory(x) ↔ (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(FlowModificationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab2067">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalPowerTransformationProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SolidStorageAndDispensingFunction">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A designed function borne by petroleum production equipment whose realization constitutes the storage of solid materials and their controlled dispensing in metered quantities into a process stream.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab1462"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab1461"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de armazenamento e distribuição de sólidos</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">solid storage and dispensing function</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab676">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
