  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InformationSignal">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">sinal de informação</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">information signal</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">An information content entity constituting a signal carrying informational content such as a measurement value or status indication within petroleum production instrumentation.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/InformationContentEntity"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/KineticMotion">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">kinetic motion</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">movimento cinético</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A process in which the directed mechanical motion of a component or fluid stream carrying kinetic energy in petroleum production equipment.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab2235">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000066"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab2591">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TransductionProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000145">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab2199"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de alívio</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">relief valve</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de alívio é uma válvula projetada para abrir automaticamente em um ponto de ajuste de pressão predeterminado para aliviar o excesso de pressão e prevenir níveis de pressão inseguros em um sistema.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A relief valve is a valve that is designed to automatically open at a predetermined pressure setpoint to relieve excess pressure and prevent unsafe pressure levels in a system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A relief valve is a valve that is designed to automatically open at a predetermined pressure setpoint to relieve excess pressure and prevent unsafe pressure levels in a system.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ReliefValve(x) ↔ (Valve(x) ∧ ∃f (PressureReliefFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every relief valve is a valve that bears a pressure relief function, which realizes a pressure relief process that automatically opens the valve when system pressure exceeds a predetermined setpoint.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab2430">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SpacingFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CuttingsAndFluid">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000024"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">fluido de cascalhos de e</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cuttings and fluid</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A material artifact that constitutes a mixture of rock cuttings and drilling fluid circulated from the wellbore bottom to the surface during drilling operations.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000282">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A fuse is an electrical equipment that protects circuits by interrupting current flow through the intentional melting of a fusible element when current exceeds specified values for a sufficient duration.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every fuse is an electrical equipment that bears a circuit protection function and has a fuse element that melts under overcurrent conditions.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fuse</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">fusível</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um fusível é um equipamento elétrico que protege circuitos interrompendo o fluxo de corrente através do derretimento intencional de um elemento fusível quando a corrente excede valores especificados por uma duração suficiente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A fuse is an electrical equipment that protects circuits by interrupting current flow through the intentional melting of a fusible element when current exceeds specified values for a sufficient duration.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Fuse(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(CircuitProtectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃e(FuseElement(e) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,e)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab1271"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000097">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (BlowDownValve(x) ↔ Valve(x) ∧ ∃f (RapidDepressurizationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A blow down valve is a valve that bears a designed function for rapid depressurization of high pressure systems.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every blow down valve is a valve that has the function of rapid depressurization.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">blow down valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de blow down</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n55b6dbcc703c488db80806efee5015fab221"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de blow down é uma válvula que possui uma função projetada para despressurização rápida de sistemas de alta pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A blow down valve is a valve that bears a designed function for rapid depressurization of high pressure systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
